This paper discusses deep learning approaches for unsupervised domain adaptation, which involves training a network on labeled data from a source domain and unlabeled data from a related but different target domain. This topic is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG), as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) since these fields often involve domain adaptation. Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) since domain adaptation is important in multimedia applications such as image and video processing.
